description: The Fund employs a passive management – or indexing – investment approach, through physical acquisition of securities, and seeks to track the performance of the Bloomberg Global Aggregate US Treasury Float Adjusted Index (the “Index”).The Fund invests in a representative sample of bonds included in the Index in order to closely match the Index’s capital and income return.The Index measures the performance of a broad spread of US dollar denominated bonds paying a fixed rate of interest issued by the US government.Bonds in the Index have maturities of greater than one year and are generally investment grade.To a lesser extent the Fund may invest in similar types of government bonds outside the Index.
name: Vanguard USD Treasury Bond UCITS ETF (USD) Distributing
